They made the discovery while raiding an illegal chop shop in Mfuleni last week, South African Police Service spokesperson Captain Frederick van Wyk said yesterday. The discovery was a result of the team acting on information they had received about alleged irregularities at premises in Great Kei Road, Happy Valley, Mfuleni. “An operation comprising of members of Crime Intelligence, Stikland VISS and Flying Squad was successful,” said Van Wyk. He said a white Kia Truck, stolen in Ocean View in August; a blue Polo Playa, the chassis number of which had been tampered with; a blue Mazda Rustler hijacked in Cape Town Central in August and white Trailer chassis (whose number was) tampered with; were recovered. Cape Times